  "title": "Introduction to the Parts of the Guitar",
  "lessonText": "Understanding your guitar's parts is essential for effective playing.",
  "data": {
    "content": "- **Body**: The main part of the guitar that produces sound.\n- **Neck**: The long part where you press the strings.\n- **Headstock**: The top of the guitar where the tuning pegs are located.\n- **Strings**: The wires that produce sound when strummed or plucked.\n- **Fretboard**: The front of the neck where the frets are placed.\n- **Bridge**: The part that holds the strings in place on the body."
  }
}
